		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, I noticed that might be an issue (with the game), so I would potentially use my development skills solely to port games over to the NES.  I'm not sure if I'd have the ambition to do it (or modifying the graphics from other consoles, such as the hypothetical Joe &amp; Mac re-conversion), but I reckon I could get some peeps to help along.  I have a good idea of what the NES' graphics are capable of, so I could probably give my colleagues some guidelines as to what the graphics should be like.  But porting games would be possibly illegal, though, which explains why there are so few 'direct ports' of games; Thwaite is adaptation of Missile Command, STREEMERZ is a port of the flash game (with Pondunkian's permission, no less).  I'm not a good game designer, and I feel the NES missed out on a few arcade classics.

		

